# The `MapVector` Class Template Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

This class implements a map that also provides access to all stored values in a deterministic order. <a href="#details">More...</a>

## Declaration

<CodeBlock>template &lt;typename KeyT, typename ValueT, typename MapType = DenseMap&lt;KeyT, unsigned&gt;, typename VectorType = SmallVector&lt;std::pair&lt;KeyT, ValueT&gt;, 0&gt;&gt;
class llvm::MapVector&lt;KeyT, ValueT, MapType, VectorType&gt;</CodeBlock>

## Description {#details}

This class implements a map that also provides access to all stored values in a deterministic order.

The values are kept in a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector">SmallVector&lt;&#42;, 0&gt;</a> and the mapping is done with <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/densemap">DenseMap</a> from Keys to indexes in that vector.

Definition at line 36 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/mapvector-h">MapVector.h</a>.

Returns an iterator to the element following the one which was removed, which may be <a href="#a0881334358ff6ff7ff8cea5562c7988e">end()</a>.
